A command line interface to manage multiple system services
ABOUT                                                                                                                                                   
This program manages (Start, Stop, Query) multiple Windows Services in a single or distributed Windows-System.
The project uses perl to build an interface to the Windows Services.
The executable program was generated using a registered version of ©Perl2exe. 
                                                                                   
Requirements
 * Rights to manage the Services (local Administrator) 

                                                                                                                                              
Installation 
 1.- Unpack win-services.zip into your selected Directory (e.g.: D:\admin) 
 2.- Create a File with the services to be managed using the format:

     # 'server' 'service'     timeout
     'server A' 'service 1'   20
     'server A' 'service 2'   5
     'server B' 'service 1'   5

    Considering the dependencies between the services, 
    you'd have to create two configuration files using a different start and stop sequence. 

 3.- Run the program (see Examples) 

                                                                                                                                       
Examples
  * Get the status without report. Only console output
     winservices -v -c -l epmsystem.start -a STATUS 

  * Start the services and write a report into D:\admin\reports
       winservices.exe -l epmsystem.start -a START -d D:\admin\reports 

